FBIS4-2169 "drchi067_b_94007" FBIS-CHI-94-067 Daily Report 7 Apr 1994 United States & Canada U.S. Oil Firm Sets Up Fund To Help With Education U.S. Oil Firm Sets Up Fund To Help With Education OW0704105494 Beijing XINHUA in English 0958 GMT 7 Apr 94 OW0704105494 Beijing XINHUA English BFN [Text] Beijing, April 7 (XINHUA) -- Mobil, a leading world oil company, is marking the 100th anniversary of its business in China by setting up a fund of 500,000 U.S. dollars to help with China's education. The corporation presented a 100,000 U.S. dollars check to the National Academy of Education Administration as the first instalment for the fund in support of the academy's efforts to upgrade the training facilities and programs for training education administrators. With its headquarters in the United States, Mobil started its Shanghai office 100 years ago and returned to China in 1974. Now it has three offices -- in Beijing, Shanghai, and Guangzhou. K. Yuan, chairman and managing director of the Mobil Corporation in Hong Kong, said that Mobil has been in China for a long time and intends to stay for a lot longer.
